<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-666-721  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 666 721.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Nov 26 1990 n494 p32(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Volkswagen unit links car makers to dealers. (V-Crest Systems Inc.andO;builds satellite-based information system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Medford, Cassimir.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Volkswagen of America Inc subsidiary V-Crest Systems Inc builds asatellite-based information system to allow automobile dealers tocommunicate with multiple manufacturers.andP;  V-Crest will act as asingle source vendor offering installation, ongoing support,network services and training.andP;  Generally, individual carmanufacturers set up exclusive networks with their dealersrequiring multi-franchise dealers to operate different computersystems for each maker.andP;  V-Crest works with Atlanta-basedScientific Atlanta Inc for its satellite expertise.andP;  The V-Crestpackage includes all the necessary hardware, software andnetworking services to run in an on-line or standalone environmentand offers accounting, marketing, sales, parts and service,finance and insurance applications.andP;  The system employs ScientificAtlanta's X.25TM very small aperture satellite system.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   V-Crest Systems Inc. (Planning).andO;Topic:     Automobile IndustryComputer Systems IntegratorsInformation SystemsSatellite CommunicationsVery Small Aperture TerminalsStrategic PlanningNetwork Architecture.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>